{
  "_comment": "redroid-seccomp.json — seccomp BPF profile pinned for ReDroid 12 L1 sandbox cells (CLO-54). Derived from the Docker default seccomp profile (moby/moby/profiles/seccomp/default.json) with explicit allow-listing of the syscalls Magisk + Android userspace require for late_start_service mount-bind operations. defaultAction is SCMP_ACT_ERRNO so any unlisted syscall returns EPERM; this is allowlist-style, not denylist. ReDroid 12 has been verified to boot under this profile when paired with /dev/binder + /dev/ashmem device passthrough and apparmor=unconfined. Do NOT relax defaultAction to SCMP_ACT_ALLOW. Do NOT add module-load syscalls (init_module, finit_module, delete_module) — those are intentionally absent and are the primary reason this profile exists. Reviewed for refuse-privileged-compose §4 compliance.",
  "_owner": "emulator-builder (8fd1506f-01cc-492b-a4d0-5e2a174fb739)",
  "_pinned_by_issue": "CLO-54",
